                                                          HTML --> DOM
                                                          
                           Only one index.html file
                           
                           source(src) -
                                 react code
                                 
                                                                
                                 
                DOM:
                   true structure
                   
       babel : javascript compiler
               is used to convert old version of javascript to new version
               
       jsx   : javascript syntax
               but it looks like html but not html
               
           javascript long code to react short code
           imperative to declarative style
           How ever backend react uses javascript behind the scene
           
           
           software for react: 
                           1. nodejs
                           2. npm javascript package manager(library) it already comes with node
                           3. react development tool extension in browser
                                                                                   
                                 
            why App.js?
            
                  It is a root component of all component
                  
            what is JSX?
                  It is look like html but not a html
                  if You want write js code inside the jsx(html) use {}
                  we can't use direct object inside {}            eg: {{name:"name",age:12}} not allowed
                  we can't use logical true value inside {}       eg: {1 === 1} not allowed
                  
                                          Functional Component
                                          
                  component name file name should start with Capital
                  Always use seperate seperate component it reduce the code redentency
                  Reuse the code again and again
                  Not neccesary to use <div></div> inside the function 
                  
                                          CSS-style(style = {jsObjectname})
                                          
                 Inline & Internal:
                 Inline css in functional component is like object in js
                 we have to create js object and store key value(backgroundColor:blue)
                 or else directly declare eg: style = {{backgroundColor:blue,...}}                                        
                 
                 External :
                 External css is writing in another file and import it and use the class name in className = "classname"                 
                 
                                       
                                                  Event(sambavam)(reverse process in javascript(documnet.getElementById('idname')))
                                                  
                1. onClick it execute the method when you click on respective button
                         syntax onClick = {(e)=>functionName()} - work
                                onClick = {(e)=>functionName}   - work
                                onClick = {functionName()}     - not work, this will execute during the compile time
                                                                             
                                 
                                 
                                 
